de.wwu.muggl.symbolic.testCases
Class TestCaseSolutionEliminationWrap

java.lang.Object
  de.wwu.muggl.symbolic.testCases.TestCaseSolutionEliminationWrap
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Comparable<TestCaseSolutionEliminationWrap>
 class TestCaseSolutionEliminationWrap
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<TestCaseSolutionEliminationWrap>

This class wraps a TestCaseSolution in order to ease the elimination process when generating the final set test cases. It therefore contains a TestCaseSolution and forwards the methods to get the def-use and control flow coverage mappings. It introduced two additional fields. They are uses to store the number of def-use chains and control graph edges which are covered by the solution wrapped. If another solution was picked to be included in the final set of test cases, this numbers can be decreased as they only have to reflect the number of yet uncovered chains and edges, i.e. those, that are not covered by the already picked solution(s) but are covered by the one wrapped here.

Keeping track of these numbers means some initial effort and decreasing them after picking a solution is a rather slow process. However, finding the next suitable solution is sped up greatly. This justifies the minor increase in memory needed for these wrapper objects.

Note: this class has a natural ordering that is inconsistent with equals.

The class has package visibility only as it is meant to be utilized by the SolutionProcessor.

Version:
1.0.0, 2010-03-10
Author:
Tim Majchrzak
